						<div class="postbody">After reading this post I still have a few questions:<br /><br />1. So I only need to load the pattern tables from CHR-ROM and the rest of the tables will be filled up by the program code (I assume by writing values to $2006?)?  I'm still a bit fuzzy on how the attribute and nametables are filled.  <br />2. Where exactly is the CHR data located inside of the ROM file?  I know that PRG data starts after the iNes header, but what address does the CHR data start and end at?<br />3. How do I go about rendering one image at a time instead of running the PPU in parallel with the CPU?  Do I just run the CPU until enough cycles have passed for one frame to be drawn and then have the PPU draw the frame from the data in VRAM at that moment?  Won't the PPU miss changes to it's registers since it will only be checking them once per frame?</div>

